@ThinkingandTinkering 
Wow, he repeated an often-told falsehood about the "space pen."  There is more to the story, but I kept it as brief as possible.  The Soviets ended up buying Fisher space pens for their astronauts to use as well.  Pencils cause real problems with graphite dust and pieces getting in electrical circuits.
I have owned a few of them and used them for several years.  The ink is under pressure and that causes it to ooze slightly around the ball.  The first little bit of writing you do leaves a glob of ink on the paper.  I eventually stopped using them because of that.
